@subsubsection Transaction Information Request

@subsubheading @prim{TR_INFO_REQ}

This primitive request the TR provider to return the values of all supported protocol parameters
(@pxref{TR_INFO_ACK}), and also the current state of the TR provider (as defined in @ref{State/Event
Tables}).  This primitive does not affect the state of the TR provider and does not appear in the
state tables.

@subsubheading Format

The format of the message is one @prim{M_PCPROTO} message block and its structure is as follows:

@display
@verbatim
typedef struct TR_info_req {
    ulong PRIM_type;          /* Always TR_INFO_REQ */
} TR_info_req_t;
@end verbatim
@tpindex TR_info_req_t
@end display

@subsubheading Parameters

The primitive has the following arguments:

@table @parm

@item PRIM_type
Indicates the primitive type.  Always @prim{TR_INFO_REQ}.

@end table

@subsubheading Modes

Both connection-mode and connectionless-mode.

@subsubheading Originator

Transaction user.

@subsubheading Valid States

This primitive is valid in any state where a local acknowledgement is not pending.

@subsubheading New State

The new state remains unchanged.

@subsubheading Rules

For the rules governing the requests made by this primitive, see the @prim{TR_INFO_ACK} primitive
described in @ref{TR_INFO_ACK}.

@subsubheading Acknowledgements

This primitive requires the TR provider to generate one of the following acknowledgements upon
receipt of the primitive and that the TR user wait for the acknowledgement before issuing any other
primitives:

@itemize ---

@item @emph{Successful:} Correct acknowledgement of the primitive is indicated with the
@prim{TR_INFO_ACK} primitive described in @ref{TR_INFO_ACK}.

@item @emph{Non-fatal Errors:} These errors will be indicated with the @prim{TR_ERROR_ACK} primitive
described in @ref{TR_ERROR_ACK}.  The allowable errors are as follows:

There are no errors associated with the issuance of this primitive.

@end itemize 

