@node TR_ADDR_ACK
@subsubsection Transaction Protocol Address Acknowledgement

@subsubheading @prim{TR_ADDR_ACK}

This primitive indicates to the TR user the addresses of the local and remote ASE.  The local
address is the protocol address that has been bound to the @dfn{stream}.  If an transaction
association has been established, the remote address is the protocol address of the remote ASE.

@subsubheading Format

The format of the message is one @prim{M_PCPROTO} message block structured as follows:

@display
@verbatim
typedef struct TR_addr_ack {
    long PRIM_type;           /* always TR_ADDR_ACK */
    long LOCADDR_length;      /* length of local address */
    long LOCADDR_offset;      /* offset of local address */
    long REMADDR_length;      /* length of remote address */
    long REMADDR_offset;      /* offset of remote address */
} TR_addr_ack_t;
@end verbatim
@tpindex TR_addr_ack_t
@end display

@subsubheading Parameters

The primitive has the following arguments:

@table @parm

@item PRIM_type
Indicates the primitive type.  Always @prim{TR_ADDR_ACK}.

@item LOCADDR_length
Indicates the length of the protocol address that was bound to the @dfn{stream}.

@item LOCADDR_offset
Indicates the offset from the beginning of the @prim{M_PCPROTO} message block where the protocol
address begins.

@item REMADDR_length
Indicates the length of the protocol address of the remote ASE.

@item REMADDR_offset
Indicates the offset from the beginning of the @prim{M_PCPROTO} message block where the protocol
address begins.

@end table

The proper alignement of the addresses in the @prim{M_PCPROTO} message block is not guaranteed.

@subsubheading Modes

Both connection-mode and connectionless-mode.

@subsubheading Originator

Transaction provider.

@subsubheading Valid State

This primitive is issued in response to a @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ} primitive and is valid in any state
where a response is pending to a @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ}.

@subsubheading New State

The new state remains unchanged.

@subsubheading Rules

The following rules apply:

@itemize ---

@item If the requested transaction identifier was @samp{-1} in the corresponding @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ}
primitive, and the transaction endpoint is not bound to a local address, (i.e. it is in the
@psta{TRS_UNINIT} or @psta{TRS_UNBND} state) the @parm{LOCADDR_length} and @parm{LOCADDR_offset}
fields must be set to @samp{0}.

@item If the requested transaction exists as identifed in the corresponding @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ}
primitive, @parm{LOCADDR_length} and @parm{LOCADDR_offset} fields will be populated to reflect the
local association address for the specified transaction.

@item If the requested transaction identifier was @samp{-1} in the corresponding @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ}
primitive, the @parm{REMADDR_length} and @parm{REMADDR_offset} fields must be set to @samp{0}.

@item If the requested transaction exists as identified in the corresponding @prim{TR_ADDR_REQ}
primitive, @parm{REMADDR_length} and @parm{REMADDR_offset} fields will be populated to reflect the
remote association address for the specified transaction.

@end itemize

