@node TR_CONT_IND
@subsubsection Transaction Continue Indication

@subsubheading @prim{TR_CONT_IND}

This transaction provider originated primitive indicates to the transaction user that this message
contains transaction user data.  As in the @prim{TR_CONT_REQ} primitive (@pxref{TR_CONT_REQ}), the
TSDU can eb segmented into more than one TIDU.  The TIDUs are assocated with the TSDU by using the
@pval{TR_MORE_DATA_FLAG}.  The @pval{TR_RC_FLAG} and @pval{TR_NO_PERMISSION} flags are allowed to be
set only on the last TIDU.  Use of the @prim{M_PROTO} message blocks is optional (see guidelines
describe in @pxref{TR_CONT_REQ}).

@subsubheading Format

The format of the message is one @prim{M_PROTO} message block, followed by zero or more
@prim{M_DATA} message blocks containing user data for the association, structured as follows:

@display
@verbatim
typedef struct TR_cont_ind {
    ulong PRIM_type;          /* Always TR_CONT_IND */
    ulong TRANS_id;           /* Transaction id */
    ulong ASSOC_flags;        /* Association flags */
    ulong OPT_length;         /* Options structure length */
    ulong OPT_offset;         /* Options structure offset */
} TR_cont_ind_t;
@end verbatim
@tpindex TR_cont_ind_t
@end display

@subsubheading Parameters

The primitive has the following arguments:

@table @parm

@item PRIM_type
Indicates the primitive type: always @prim{TR_CONT_IND}.

@item TRANS_id
Indicates the transaction identifier previously indicated by the transport provider to uniquely
identify the transaction.  The transaction identifier must be indicated by the transaction provider.
The transaction identifier must be the same as the transaction identifier that was indicated in the
corresponding @prim{TR_BEGIN_IND} or @prim{TR_BEGIN_CON}.

@item ASSOC_flags
Specifies the option flags provided with the primitive.  See ``Flags'' below.  Some flags may be
provider specific.

@item OPT_length
Indicates the length of the protocol options associated with the user data transfer.  Protocol
options are only indicated by the transaction provider when they were supplied by the underlying
protocol.  If the transport provider does not indicate protocol options, the @parm{OPT_length} and
@parm{OPT_offset} fields must be set to zero (0).  The format of the protocol options are provider
specific.

@item OPT_offset
Indicates the offset from the beginning of the @prim{M_PROTO} message block where the protocol
options begin.

@end table

@subsubheading Flags


@table @pval

@item TR_MORE_DATA_FLAG
When set, indicates taht the next @prim{TR_CONT_IND} message (TIDU) is part of this TSDU.

@item TR_RC_FLAG
The value of the flag may indicate either that confirmation is requested or that it is not
requested.  The flag is allowed to be set only if use of the Receipt Confirmation was agreed between
both the transaction users and the transaction provider during transaction association
establishment.  The value of this flag is always identical to that supplied in the corresponding
@prim{TR_CONT_REQ}.

@item TR_NO_PERMISSION
The value of this flag may indicate either that the transaction peer gives permission (clear) to end
the transaction association or does not give permission (set) to end the transaction association.
This flag is only valid for transaction providers that support it (@pxref{Addendum for ANSI
Conformance}).

@end table

@subsubheading Valid State

This primitive is valid in transaction state @psta{TRS_DATA_XFER}.  This primitive is only valid in
connection-oriented mode.

@subsubheading New State

The new state for the transaction is unchanged.

@subsubheading Rules


@itemize ---

@item When the @prim{TR_NO_PERMISSION} flag is set, the transaction user must not issue a
@prim{TR_END_REQ} primitive in response to this indication.

@end itemize

