@subsubheading SCCP Quality of Service Options

The TCAP interface uses protocol level @pval{T_SS7_SCCP} for options at the SCCP level.  SCCP QoS
parameters are communicated to the underlying transaction provider using the option name
@pval{T_SCCP_QOS}.  There are three QoS structure that can be used in this fashion as follows:

@center @image{tri_tabn}

Quality of service struct @var{N_qos_sel_sccp_t} has the following fields:

@table @var

@item n_qos_type
This is the NPI Quality of Service structure type and is always set to @pval{N_QOS_SEL_SCCP},
@pval{N_QOS_OPT_SEL_SCCP}, or @pval{N_QOS_RANGE_SCCP}.

@item protocol_class
This is the protocol class.  The @var{protocol_class} field can be one of the following:

@itemize @bullet

@item @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_0} (SCCP connectionless protocol class 0),

@item @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_1} (for SCCP connectionless protocol class 1),

@item @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_2} (for SCCP connection-oriented protocol class 2),

@item @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_3} (for SCCP connection-oriented protocol class 3) or

@item @pval{QOS_UNKNOWN}.

@end itemize

@pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_2} and @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_3} are not applicable to TCAP.

@item option_flags
If the @var{options_flags} field has bit @pval{N_QOS_OPT_RETERR} set then the SCCP will return the
PDU on error.

@item importance
This is the importance of the message for consideration for SCCP flow control.  This value is not
normally set by the user.  It can be any integer number from 0 to 7, or @pval{QOS_UNKNOWN}.

@item sequence_selection
This affects the SLS (Signalling Link Selection) value that will be used for protocol classes
@pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_0} and @pval{N_QOS_PCLASS_1}.  This value is not normally set by the user and can
be an integer value or @pval{QOS_UNKNOWN}.

@item message_priority
This affects the MP (Message Priority) value that will be used for specific messages in all protocol
classes.  This value is not normally set by the use and can be any integer value from 0 to 3 or the
value @pval{QOS_UNKNOWN}.

@end table

